;; **
;;; As shown above, graphs are identified with a unique ID. To use them in programs, we can always define a _var_ to refer to a graph. The statement below defines a _var_ that refers to an empty graph.
;;; 
;;; > Note: if you are not familiar with Clojure, you can think of vars are similar to variables in other languages.
;; **

;; @@
(def g0 (newgrape))
;; @@
;; =>
;;; {"type":"html","content":"<span class='clj-var'>#&#x27;tutorial/g0</span>","value":"#'tutorial/g0"}
