;; **
;;; Is this rule applicable to graph `g1`? The answer to this question depends on the matching semantics. If **_non-injective_** matches are allowed, the two `Hello` nodes in rule `rel` may in fact be matched to the _same_ node in the graph the rule is applied to. 
;;; 
;;; The match is illustrated in the following figure:
;;; 
;;; ![](https://github.com/jenshweber/grape/blob/master/help/match.png?raw=true)
;;; 
;;; 
