;; **
;;; ##### Gluing condition
;;; 
;;; In practice, the identification condition is often used in combination with the dangling condition. Rules that enforce both conditions are are _reversible_. Due to the importance and practical relevance of these properties, the _gluing condition_ is defined as the combination of the identity condition and the dangling condition.
;; **

;; @@
(rule delworld-safe2 []
      (global GLUE)
      (read (node w:World))
      (delete w))
;; @@
