;; **
;;; #### Local application conditions
;;; 
;;; Local application conditions can be added to rules to further restrict matches. We will talk about such application conditions later in this tutorial. However, as a preview, here is a rule (`rel3`) that uses an application condition to ensure that two different nodes are matched for `h` and `h2`. Since `rel3` only has two nodes, its semantics is the same as that of rule `rel2`:
;; **

;; @@
(rule rel3 [] 
   (read
       (node h:Hello)
       (node h2:Hello)
       (condition "not h=h2"))
   (create 
       (edge :rel h h2)))
