;;; ### Atomicity
;;; Atomicity is the property that guarantees that a sequence of operations is performed entirely or not at all. _GrapeVine_'s fully persistent data structure guarantees that previous versions of the graph remain available in case a sequence of operations is interrupted.
;;; 
;;; ### Consistency
;;; _GrapeVine_ checks consistency constraints / schema constraints after each graph transformation. This is different from the typical approach of checking schema constraints only at the end of a transaction. A planned future version of _GrapeVine_ will provide this functionality.
;;; 
;;; ### Isolation
;;; Given _GrapeVine_'s functional approach to graph computation, concurrent transactions are automatically isolated from each other. They result in separate _version branches_ of a graph's derivation history. What is missing currently is a way to merge these parallel branches back into a single graph state. This is subject to current work.
